t3368.text: The past few dreams, I’ve taken my husband and children there. The hut became a large building made of glass, and there were other people’s trinkets there too. People had written in the diary I left, with their own thoughts and memories of events. It was comforting.

t3369.text: The second is a mountain. The first dreams I had about it, there was a small empty hut at the summit where I left some small trinkets, things that are/were important to me IRL. I always went alone.

t3370.text: There’s also a GIANT pool in the backyard, and the garage is the one my husband and I lived in when we were engaged. (It was converted to a granny flat IRL) The real-world location is where my dad’s friend lives. I spent a lot of time there as a kid

t3371.text: The first is this gorgeous house, with architecture that seems normal in the dream but makes no sense in the waking world. The top bedroom is mine (usually) and overlooks the rest of the house. Sometimes there’s stairs leading to it, sometimes an elevator.
